President Jacob Zuma has appointed a permanent SABC board following pressure from lobby groups and some political parties. Media Monitoring Africa andÂ SOS Support Public Broadcasting Coalition had filed an urgent application in the high court in a bid to force the president to appoint a permanent board. Zuma had until close of business on Monday to oppose the application, but he missed the deadline. The Economic Freedom Fighters had also threatened to take the president to court if he did not appoint a permanent board. The following people have been appointed for a period of five years, with immediate effect, the Presidency said: Makhathini will be the chairperson of the board and Potgieter-Gqubule will be the deputy chairperson, the Presidency said. More to follow.